olive oil
1 corn
2 Burger Bun
1 avocado
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Kiwi Spice Blend
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
20 g butter
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Preheat BBQ to high heat.
• Halve corn and burger buns.
• Slice avocado in half, scoop out flesh and thinly slice. Season with salt and pepper.

• In a large bowl, combine beef mince, Kiwi spice blend, fine breadcrumbs and the egg.
• Shape beef mixture into 2cm-thick patties (1 per person).

• When BBQ is hot, add corn to BBQ and cook, turning, until charred and cooked through, 10-15 minutes.
• In the last minute of cook time, sprinkle over shredded Cheddar cheese. Cover with a lid or foil so the cheese melts.
• Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.

NO BBQ? In a medium saucepan, bring water to boil. Cook corn in boiling water until tender and bright yellow, 5 minutes. Transfer to a plate, the sprinkle over Cheddar cheese. Cover to keep warm.

• Meanwhile, grill beef patties for 3-5 minutes each side, until charred and cooked through.

NO BBQ? Cook beef patties in a frying pan over high heat, 4-5 minutes each side.

• When the patties are done, grill buns, cut-side down, until lightly golden, 2-3 minutes.

NO BBQ? Grill or toast buns to your liking.

• In a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil.
• Top corn with butter.
• Spread base of burger buns with mayonnaise, then top with smokey beef patty, avocado and salad leaves.
• Serve with cheesy buttered corn cob. Enjoy!